<subSubSection pageId="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,541,925]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,541,566]" pageId="7">Description.</emphasis>
Crown white with brown diamond-shaped spot at apex; pronotum white and semitransparent, anterior margin white, other parts indistinctly brown; scutellum pale yellow, basal triangles on scutum brown; face yellowish white, frontoclypeal area broad, anteclypeus somewhat pentagonal, lorum narrow; forewing sordid white without distinct dark markings preapically, margin of apical angle brown (Figs. 
<number box="[1045,1089,649,673]" pageId="7" value="3.8">3, 8</number>
, 
<number box="[1101,1174,649,673]" pageId="7" value="13.18">13, 18</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,541,925]" pageId="7">
Pygofer caudally broadly rounded, with 
<number box="[649,704,685,709]" pageId="7" value="9.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="8.0">8–11</number>
dorso-apical macrosetae, ventral appendage well developed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 67" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,990,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[185,1402,978,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 67. Oniella albula (Cai &amp; Shen), n. comb.: 62, male pygofer, lateral view; 63, subgenital plate, lateral view; 64, aedeagus, posteroventral view; 65, aedeagus, lateral view; 66, connective dorsal view; 67, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217881/files/figure.png" pageId="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,721,745]" pageId="7" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate long, tapering apicad, with row of 
<number box="[774,816,721,745]" pageId="7" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
macrosetae as single row, numerous fine setae sparsely distributed over surface laterad of macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[690,776,757,781]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 67" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,990,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[185,1402,978,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 67. Oniella albula (Cai &amp; Shen), n. comb.: 62, male pygofer, lateral view; 63, subgenital plate, lateral view; 64, aedeagus, posteroventral view; 65, aedeagus, lateral view; 66, connective dorsal view; 67, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217881/files/figure.png" pageId="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[745,776,757,781]" pageId="7" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style narrowing apicad (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1165,757,781]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 67" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,990,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[185,1402,978,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 67. Oniella albula (Cai &amp; Shen), n. comb.: 62, male pygofer, lateral view; 63, subgenital plate, lateral view; 64, aedeagus, posteroventral view; 65, aedeagus, lateral view; 66, connective dorsal view; 67, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217881/files/figure.png" pageId="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1134,1165,757,781]" pageId="7" value="67.0">67</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped, arms short, 
<number box="[285,295,793,817]" pageId="7" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[306,320,793,817]" pageId="7" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as stem (
<figureCitation box="[520,606,793,817]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 67" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,990,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[185,1402,978,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 67. Oniella albula (Cai &amp; Shen), n. comb.: 62, male pygofer, lateral view; 63, subgenital plate, lateral view; 64, aedeagus, posteroventral view; 65, aedeagus, lateral view; 66, connective dorsal view; 67, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217881/files/figure.png" pageId="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[574,606,793,817]" pageId="7" value="66.0">66</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus broad and short, aedeagal shaft curved dorsad, with a pair of long, slender curved appendages arising from ventral part of expanded atrium and slightly surpassing shaft apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,865,889]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 67" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,990,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[185,1402,978,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 67. Oniella albula (Cai &amp; Shen), n. comb.: 62, male pygofer, lateral view; 63, subgenital plate, lateral view; 64, aedeagus, posteroventral view; 65, aedeagus, lateral view; 66, connective dorsal view; 67, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217881/files/figure.png" pageId="7">
Figs. 
<number box="[223,297,865,889]" pageId="7" value="64.5" valueMax="65.0" valueMin="64.0">64–65</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,541,925]" box="[199,1330,901,925]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,901,925]" pageId="7">Measurements.</emphasis>
