<subSubSection pageId="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,356]" pageId="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[572,656,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Oniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[572,656,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8">Oniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this species is the palest, with the forewing lacking dark patches; this may be the reason Cai &amp; Shen (
<number box="[504,562,367,391]" pageId="8" value="1998.0">1998</number>
) placed it in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[821,927,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,927,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="8">Sophonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this species has a long and narrow subgenital plate and the frontoclypeal area broad. These features are not present in the genus 
<emphasis box="[1198,1312,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="8">
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1308,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sophonia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Therefore, this species is transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[469,553,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Oniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[469,553,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="8">Oniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
